 Nearly half of the first floor and part of the loft of a two-storey terraced home caught alight in London, however, no injuries have been reported. The fire was under control by 18:37, officers announced. The London Fire Brigade (LFB) was called at 17:28 Monday evening to the home on Arnold road.  Teams from Tottenham, Walthamstow, Holloway and nearby fire stations helped tackle the house fire, a statement said.  "Nearly half of the first floor and part of the loft of a two-storey terraced house was damaged by fire.  